'''Siaka Bamba''' (born 24 August 1989), is an [[Ivory Coast|Ivorian]] footballer who plays as a [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfielder]] for [[Lusitano de Évora|Lusitano Ginásio Clube]].

In the summer of 2013, Bamba rejoined former side [[G.D. Chaves|Desportivo de Chaves]].<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/Futebol/Nacional/interior.aspx?content_id=841897 Como foi o último dia de mercado em Portugal (How was the last day of the market in Portugal)]; [[Record (newspaper)|Record]], 3 September 2013. Retrieved 4 June 2014 {{pt icon}}</ref>

Whilst at Feirense, Bamba won the [[SJPF Segunda Liga Player of the Month]] for March 2011.<ref>[http://clubedesportivofeirense.blogspot.co.uk/2011_04_01_archive.html Prémios para o Feirense (Awards for Feirense)]; CD Feirense Blogspot, 28 April 2011. Retrieved 4 June 2014 {{pt icon}}</ref>

Bamba represented his country at the [[2005 FIFA U-17 World Championship]]. During the tournament which saw his side finish bottom of their group, Bamba scored a goal for his country in a 1–1 draw with the United States.<ref>[http://www.zerozero.pt/edition.php?id_edicao=1118&fase=11880&grupo=435 Campeonato do Mundo Sub-17 2005 (U-17 World Championship)]; ZeroZero, Retrieved 4 June 2014 {{pt icon}}</ref>

In [[2018–19 C.R.D. Libolo season|2018–19]], he signed in for [[C.R.D. Libolo|Recreativo do Libolo]] in Angola's premier league, the Girabola.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.angop.ao/angola/pt_pt/noticias/desporto/2018/9/42/Girabola2018-Recreativo-Libolo-PLANTEL,33dff2a7-dd77-458f-a467-325dc1fb5f2b.html |title=Girabola2018/19: Recreativo do Libolo - PLANTEL |date=24 October 2014|accessdate=22 Dec 2018|publisher=ANGOP Angolan News Agency |language=pt}}</ref>

In 2019-20 he signed in for [[Lusitano Ginásio Clube]] from Évora.

